# Component File Content

A component file should contain the component itself (and small local helpers only if truly component-specific). Static data and pure helpers belong elsewhere.

- **Static data** (arrays of config, copy, feature lists, perk items, etc.) → `src/lib/constants.ts`. Define a type and a named constant (e.g. `SUBSCRIPTION_PERK_ITEMS`, `PLANS`).
- **Pure helpers** (mapping plan to id, formatting, predicates) → `src/lib/utils.ts` or a focused util file.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD – data and helper in component file
const perkItems = [
  { title: "Cancel anytime", description: "...", icon: ShieldCheck },
  // ...
];
function getPackageId(plan: Plan) {
  return plan.name === "Monthly" ? "monthly" : "yearly";
}
export function SubscriptionPage() { ... }
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – component only, imports from lib
import { SUBSCRIPTION_PERK_ITEMS } from "@/lib/constants";
import { getPackageId } from "@/lib/utils";
export function SubscriptionPage() { ... }
```

Keep component files focused on JSX and component logic. Reusable data and pure functions live in `src/lib/constants.ts` and `src/lib/utils.ts`.
